# Goldie's Food Ordering System - Project Rules

## Tech Stack
- Backend: Node.js + Express + Mongoose (MongoDB). CommonJS modules.
- Frontend: Angular (Reactive Forms). Backend-first focus.
- Real-time: Socket.IO. Image uploads: multer (local /uploads, served static).
- Auth: JWT (jsonwebtoken) + bcrypt. Validation: express-validator. Logging: morgan.

## Architecture (MVC + Services)
- Keep server.js minimal (env, DB, Socket.IO, listen). Build the app in src/app.js.
- Layer responsibilities, never mix them:
  - routes/      -> define endpoints + attach middlewares only.
  - controllers/ -> handle req/res, call services. No business logic.
  - services/    -> pure business logic (pricing, points, tiers). No req/res.
  - models/      -> Mongoose schemas only.
  - middlewares/ -> auth, authorize, validate, error, logger.
  - validators/, utils/ (ApiError, asyncHandler, upload), sockets/, config/.
- Wrap async controllers with asyncHandler; throw ApiError; one global error handler.

## Database Principles
- Embed data owned by and read with its parent (Order.items as priced snapshots).
- Reference shared/independent data (Product.category, Order.user).
- Collections: User, Category, Product, Order, PointsTier, LoyaltyTransaction.
- Order stores name+unitPrice snapshots per item (preserve historical price).
- Loyalty: keep current balance denormalized on User.loyaltyBalance; full history
  in append-only LoyaltyTransaction collection (never embed unbounded history).
- PointsTier is data-driven: minAmount/maxAmount/pointsPercentage (1 point = 1 NIS).

## Roles & Authorization
- Guest (no account, checkout via Order.guestInfo), Customer (JWT), Admin (single
  shared account, role="admin"). Protect shop/admin routes with authorize('admin').

## Validation Strategy
- Server is the source of truth: express-validator + Mongoose schema constraints.
- Verify product existence/stock and recompute totals in services before saving.
- Angular Reactive Forms validate for UX only, never as a replacement for server checks.

## Conventions
- File naming: *.model.js, *.controller.js, *.service.js, *.routes.js, *.middleware.js.
- API base path: /api. RESTful resource routes.
- Do not commit secrets; .env is gitignored.
